==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*honaga-, *honanga-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''hunig'', Old Saxon [[honeg]] (Dutch [[honig]]), Old High German [[honag]], [[honeg]] (German [[Honig]]), Old Norse [[hunang]] (Swedish [[honung]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'hʊnɪj/

===Noun===
'''huniġ''' ''n''
# [[honey]]
#:''Swa þicce swa huniges tear'': as thick as honey from the comb.

